==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pantalet
<hw>Pan`ta*let"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Dim. of
<ets>pantaloon</ets>.]</ety> <def>One of the legs of the loose drawers
worn by children and women; a pant leg; particularly, the lower part of
such a garment, coming below the knee, often made in a separate piece;
-- chiefly in the plural.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pantaloon</ent>⟦br⟧
